## 3. Additional Pipelines - Shipment Tracker and Jump IDs

### 3.1 Shipment Tracker

- **Purpose:** Tracks real-time shipment status by making API calls to individual shipping carriers - FedEx, DHL, UPS, USPS, and others.
- **Ownership:** This is an upstream job bounded by CPSS. The source data comes from carrier APIs. The CPSS team owns the pipeline that ingests and transforms the carrier responses.
- **Frequency of work:** Not a daily working table, but you will receive periodic requests to update or fix the shipment tracker pipeline.

### 3.2 paas_jumpid (Jump ID Dimension)

- **What is a Jump ID:** A Jump ID is a unique encrypted identifier embedded in a URL. When a customer clicks on an HP advertisement - on Facebook, in an email, or within the HP app - the URL they land on contains a Jump ID.
- **This Jump ID allows HP to trace exactly:**
    1. Which advertisement the customer clicked
    2. Which platform they came from (Facebook, email, in-app, etc.)
    3. Which campaign was shown to them
    4. The exact customer journey that led to an AIP subscription
- **Pipeline:** Reads Jump ID data from Excel sources and loads it into dimension tables. Jump ID data appears in the allinplan_sub_base_ts pipeline to link subscription events to the advertisement campaign that drove them.
- **Business value:** Downstream teams use this to measure campaign effectiveness - whether a specific advertisement or campaign is actually converting app users into AIP subscribers.

