## 5. Data Storage Strategy and Retention

### 5.1 Current Storage Tier

All AIP data is stored in AWS S3 Standard storage. There is currently no data archival or retention policy in place for AIP.

| Decision                 | Rationale                                                                                       |
|--------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| No archival / tiering    | AIP is a new, highly monetised program - all data must remain instantly accessible              |
| No retention cutoff      | Program is only 2 years old; full history is needed for analysis and campaigns                  |
| Standard tier for all data| Moving to infrequent-access storage was tried but caused higher retrieval costs when analysts needed historical data |
| Future consideration     | When subscriber count reaches 2–3M, team may build aggregated data products and apply retention on raw fact tables (e.g., keep last 5–6 years) |

### 5.2 Delta Transaction Retention

Within Databricks Delta tables, a different retention applies - transactional history (Delta log), not the data itself:

1. Default Delta transaction retention: 7 days
2. allinplan_sub_base_ts uses 80 hours (bypasses the 7-day minimum via retentionDurationCheck = false)
3. This means: if data is corrupted, you can restore the table to any state within the past 80 hours

> Note: The Instant Ink program is 10+ years old and still retains all its data because it is also highly monetized. This is the precedent for AIP data strategy.

