## 7. Key Engineering Patterns from the Code Walkthrough

### 7.1 Lazy Evaluation and Action Calls

- All transformations are lazy until the final write action.
- Actions: `df.write.saveAsTable()` triggers computation.

### 7.2 Persist vs Cache

| Method      | Storage                  | When to Use                                   | Risk                       |
|-------------|--------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|----------------------------|
| df.persist()| Memory + Disk (spills)   | DataFrame called multiple times, small enough | OOM if too large           |
| df.cache()  | Memory only (default)    | Frequently accessed small DataFrames          | Data lost if executor fails|
| Temp Table  | Spark session catalog    | Need SQL access in later cells                | No perf. benefit over DataFrame |

> Code review: Cell 11 uses both cache() and temp table; likely redundant.

### 7.3 Window Functions

- Used for ranking, lag, null backfilling.
- Warning: Do not oversimplify case/window logic as data patterns are complex.

### 7.4 Schema Evolution and overwriteSchema

- Table schema is evolving; overwriteSchema is used for flexibility.
- Will move to incremental merge once stable.

