## 9. New Terms from Session 3

| Term          | Definition                                                                                 |
|---------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| SMB           | Small and Medium Business - a customer segment; SMB events are included in AIP device claims |
| SFMC          | Salesforce Marketing Cloud - HP's CRM email platform used for subscriber campaigns         |
| Jump ID       | Encrypted unique ID in a URL that traces which advertisement/campaign drove a user click   |
| PURL          | Personal URL — a customised URL sent to a specific customer for tracking their journey     |
| UTM fields    | Tracking parameters in URLs (utm_medium, utm_source, utm_campaign, etc.) for campaign attribution |
| GA            | General Availability - product released to all customers publicly (after beta phase)       |
| Beta customer | Customer who subscribed during the testing phase before the product was publicly released  |
| Tenant ID     | Subscriber identifier in HP's system - one tenant can have multiple addresses but one subscription address |
| Lazy evaluation| Spark's deferred execution model - transformations only compute when an action is triggered |
| persist()     | Materialises a DataFrame in memory+disk for reuse — use when called multiple times and small enough |
| cache()       | Materialises a DataFrame in memory only - similar to persist but memory-only by default    |
| QUALIFY       | SQL clause (like HAVING for window functions) used instead of subquery to filter on window rank results |
| overwriteSchema| Delta option to allow schema changes on write without manual DDL — used when schema is evolving |
| MTP Checklist | Move To Production checklist - HP's production readiness document tracking changes per pipeline |
| Delinquency   | Subscription cancellation due to payment failure / non-payment — a new data product is being built |
| RTP           | Real-Time Print - telemetry signal from AIP printers                                      |
| Care Pack     | HP's customer support / extended warranty program — tracked as a product type in AIP      |
| IoTPC         | IoT PC — HP's PC-as-a-Service program, larger than AIP, currently in pilot                |
| Marconi / Victoria / Narita / Smart Tag | AIP printer model names identified by product SKU format         |

